# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .env files are INTENTIONALLY TRACKED. Do NOT add `.env`, `.env.*`,
# or `*.env` patterns to this file. Emergent's deploy pipeline relies
# on the .env files being present in the repo bundle — blocking them
# silently strips production env values and causes deploys to roll back
# to the previous image without surfacing an error.
#
# KNOWN ISSUE: the deployment_agent tool has been observed re-appending
# `.env` blocking patterns automatically on each invocation. The audit
# script at /app/scripts/pre-deploy-audit.sh checks for this on every
# commit (via .husky/pre-commit) and every deploy (via package.json
# `update:prod` and `deploy:preflight`). If your push fails with the
# red "DEPLOY BLOCKED" banner, scroll up — the line numbers in the
# audit output tell you exactly which .env* patterns to delete.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
credentials.json
*.pem
*.key
.credentials
